This week, I started cycling as a regular physical activity to improve my body balance and overall fitness. Cycling was both enjoyable and beneficial for my health. I spent 30–40 minutes cycling in the morning, which helped increase my stamina and strengthen my leg muscles. It also improved my breathing and made me feel fresh throughout the day. I noticed that regular cycling reduced stress and gave me more energy for daily tasks. Along with cycling, I continued drinking enough water and eating healthy food. This week taught me that enjoyable exercise helps maintain sustainability and body balance effectively.
